\f1\fs28\b 3.12 System Modules\b0\fs24\f0\par
\fi720 The project is divided into several independent modules that work together to provide complete disaster response functionality.\par
\fi720 1. \b Graph Construction Module\b0: Reads road information from the dataset and constructs the weighted graph representing the transportation network.\par
\fi720 2. \b Route Calculation Module\b0: Implements Dijkstra's Algorithm to determine the shortest route between selected locations.\par
\fi720 3. \b Hospital Management Module\b0: Stores and retrieves hospital information, allowing rescue teams to identify nearby medical facilities.\par
\fi720 4. \b Shelter Management Module\b0: Maintains information regarding available emergency shelters for disaster victims.\par
\fi720 5. \b Rescue Team Module\b0: Stores rescue team information and supports emergency resource management.\par
\fi720 6. \b Disaster Information Module\b0: Maintains disaster-related data used by the application for simulation purposes.\par
\fi720 7. \b User Interface Module\b0: Provides an interactive dashboard for selecting locations, displaying maps, and visualizing computed routes.\par
\fi720 8. \b Data Management Module\b0: Loads and manages CSV datasets containing roads, hospitals, shelters, rescue teams, and geographical coordinates.\par

