\f1\fs32\b CHAPTER 5\par\par
RESULTS\b0\fs24\f0\par\par
\f1\fs28\b 5.1 Introduction\b0\fs24\f0\par
\fi720 The Disaster Response & Rescue Navigation System was successfully designed and implemented. Testing was carried out using the project datasets containing road networks, hospitals, shelters, rescue teams, and geographical coordinates. The results indicate that the system performs the required operations accurately.\par

\f1\fs28\b 5.2 System Implementation\b0\fs24\f0\par
\fi720 The project consists of the Web Frontend (HTML5, CSS3, JS, Leaflet.js) which handles selections and visualizations, and the Backend (C++) which reads CSV datasets, constructs the graph, runs pathfinders, and sends back results via Node.js.\par

\f1\fs28\b 5.3 Functional Results\b0\fs24\f0\par
\fi720 The application successfully performs: Route Calculation (Dijkstra optimal routes), Hospital and Shelter Identification (loading locations and resource metrics correctly), and Graph Traversal (verifying network connectivity using BFS/DFS).\par

\f1\fs28\b 5.4 User Interface Results\b0\fs24\f0\par
\fi720 The developed dashboard provides an intuitive interface, showing the interactive map canvas, control sidebars, hospital metrics, and alert banners.\par

